The default life schema and hygiene patterns originate from the LifeGraph
application (private predecessor at github.com/JonOnEarth/lifegraph), and are
released here under the same Apache-2.0 terms.

This work draws conceptual influence from prior art (cited in the README) but
is an independent implementation:

  - Conway, M. A. (2000). The construction of autobiographical memories
    in the self-memory system. Psychological Review, 107(2), 261–288.
  - Pink, M., et al. (2025). "Position: Episodic Memory is the Missing Piece
    for Long-Term LLM Agents." arXiv:2502.06975.
  - Sumers, T. R., et al. (2023). "Cognitive Architectures for Language
    Agents (CoALA)." arXiv:2309.02427.
  - Zep / Graphiti (https://github.com/getzep/graphiti) — episode model
    and bi-temporal edge invalidation are independently re-implemented;
    Graphiti is Apache-2.0.
  - Google LangExtract (https://github.com/google/langextract) — the
    examples=[...] few-shot authoring surface and char_interval grounding
    pattern are independently re-implemented; LangExtract is Apache-2.0.

The name "LifeGraph" was previously used in:
  - Tominski, H., & Aigner, W. (2020). "LifeGraph: A Visual Analytics
    System for Personal Data." (ACM)
This package is unrelated to that research artifact.
